@node "Instructions"

                OnLineHelp V1.2 - Kevin Winspear 1994

OnLineHelp: Introduction

        This program was made as part of `Introducing WB and AmigaDOS`, for
the people who have HardDrive`s, and is Licenceware.

        OnLineHelp is for people how have a HardDrive, it needs an ASSIGN
to work as it needs to know where the O.L.H.Files are, If you click on 
it's Icon now without installing it you will get a requester saying,
Please insert volume O.L.H.Files: in any drive.
See HD Install for more info.

        OnLineHelp is an easy-to-use Amiga OnLine Reference program.
I wrote this program because I kept getting AmigaDOS commands wrong.

        Since making the program I have added  AmigaGuides files on all
the Workbench Menus, Tool, Preferences, Commodities, Utilities and not for
getting about 80 AmigaDOS commands.
        All the information is AmigaGuide files format for quick reference.
        OnLineHelp program itself is small in size (around 20K PowerPacked)
and is specifically designed to deliver you with the minimum amount of fuss
a quick onLine Reference.

        OnLineHelp is a Commoditie program. When first loaded a window
opens with some info when you've read it click on the OK Gadget to close
the window, after the window is closed there are no more windows, just
press the HELP key (on the right side of the keyboard) to bring up the 
OnLineHelp Guides, to Quit the program you press the Left SHIFT Key and 
the ESCAPE key together (on the left side of the keyboard), you will be 
asked to comfirm this. This way it will not clutter up the Workbench.
        To close the AmigaGuide window click on the close button on the
top left corner, This dose not exit the OnLineHelp.
                    
