@endnode
@node "HD_Install"
                              Install

     Installer and Installer project icon
     (c) Copyright 1991-93 Commodore-Amiga, Inc.  All Rights Reserved.
     Reproduced and distributed under license from Commodore.

  Boot up your HardDrive first, then insert the ExtrasX.X disk your drive.

Simply double-click on the `InstallOnLineHelp' icon, After a few moments
the installer will step you through the installation procedure.

OnLineHelp: Assignment

OnLineHelp requires assignment O.L.H.Files:. If you install using the
provided installer program the assignment will be added to your
user-startup script.

You can choice where you want to put OnLineHelp Program, the default is
SYS:WBStartup, so it is there everytime you boot up.

You can also choice where you want to put O.L.H.Files Directory,
the default is WORK:.

MANUAL:-

 You can drag the OnLineHelp program any where you like, to start it just
double click on it's icon.

 You can drag the O.L.H.Files draw containing all the files any were you
like, just don't for get to put the Assign in your s:user-startup script.

                Assign O.L.H.Files: <FULL PATH>:O.L.H.Files

        You also need Amigaguide.Libaray and Commodities.Library in your 
HD Workbench:Libs directory and AmigaGuide in your HD Workbench:C 
directory.
        These are on the Workbenchx.x disk 1 of these two disks, you can
see these by booting up your HD and inserting Workbenchx.x in your drive 
and Double-click on the Workbenchx.x disk icon and then go in the 
Menus-Window and select Show All and then find the Libs directory and open 
it and you will see Amigaguide.Libaray and Commodities.Libaray, now do the 
same to your HD Workbench libs: directory and then click and drag them 
over. Do the same with the C directory and click and drag  AmigaGuide into
your HD Workbench c: directory. 

